The paper deals with auction design, which is a classic topic in game theory (cs.GT) and algorithmic mechanism design (cs.AI). The problem involves making allocation decisions in an online setting, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the subfield of online algorithms (cs.DS). The use of approximation factors and the study of optimal approximation suggest that information theory (cs.IT) may also be relevant. Overall, the paper seems to fit well within the intersection of these subfields, with a focus on auction design and online algorithms.
